The problem will be in asynchronous functions and loading state.

`loading` in store is initially set to true. In the first render is it ok. Only the first part of condition is evaluated (`loading`), the second part (`!user.name`) is skipped.
**I think you need to set `loading` back to true for the time you are waiting for asynchronous response.** This is usually done in way:

 1. Set `loading` to true (synchronously) before calling asynchronus function (this part is missing - you need another action and action type for this). 
 2. After you get response from the asynchronous function, you set `loading` to false (you already do this).


```js
 useEffect(()=&gt;{
            getCurrentProfile();
           // this is asynchronous function, the user is not loaded right after you call getUser.
           // Hence the user from props could be not initalized (still set to null).
           // This is why you are getting that error in the next lines (`setFormData`).
            getUser();
            setFormData({
                name: loading || !user.name ? &#39;&#39; : user.name,
                email: loading || !user.email ? &#39;&#39; : user.email,
                avatar: loading || !user.avatar ? &#39;&#39; : user.avatar,
            });
        }, [loading]);
```

